# Shell tooling (`bin/`)

`bin/dispatch-kimi` is a symlink to the shared `external-agent-protocol` skill's `dispatch-agent`: upstream tooling, not repo-local, so do not edit it in place. Any other scripts added under `bin/` are **zsh** by default; match the conventions below.

## Zsh

- Shebang: `#!/usr/bin/env zsh`
- Arrays are 1-indexed; use glob qualifiers and extended parameter expansion

## Bash (if used elsewhere)

- Shebang: `#!/usr/bin/env bash`
- `set -euo pipefail`
- Quote variables: `"${var}"`; use `local` in functions
- Errors to stderr: `echo "Error: ..." >&2`

## Dispatch changes

When changing Kimi dispatch or external-agent behavior:

- Dispatch mechanics live in the shared `external-agent-protocol` skill toolkit (`~/.dotfiles/skills/external-agent-protocol/`), not in this repo. Change them there.
- lbkmk-specific execution rules live in **`docs/external-agent-protocol-local.md`**; plans handed to external implementers must reference the standing protocol (see **`CLAUDE.md`**)

Do not embed Cursor-specific instructions in dispatch scripts.
